  "prompt": "What is the speed of light in a vacuum dependent on?",
  "response": "The speed of light in a vacuum, often denoted as \"c,\" is a fundamental constant of the universe and is not dependent on any other factors. It is always approximately 299,792,458 meters per second. This means that the speed of light in a vacuum does not change based on the motion of the source emitting the light or the motion of the observer measuring the speed of the light. This principle is a cornerstone of Einstein's theory of relativity.",
